How to choose the mattress and the box spring: women and men look for different things
Nothing of a pompous frame for the bed; what really gives its quality to a good bed is the surface to lie down, that is, the mattress and the box spring.
First of all, they must be complemented perfectly so that they adapt to specific users.
During the election, numerous elements come into play, including the weight, height, state of health and sex of the owner.
Also important is the type of interior in which the mattress and the box spring are located.
A typical example?
For example, in a weekend cabin that does not usually have heating, latex mattresses should not be used because they "heat up" more slowly.
In addition, they tend to weigh considerably more than the usual polyurethane mattresses.
Therefore, it is necessary to turn them around more frequently.
If the central channels are not properly aerated and, above, they are on a firm basis, they keep moisture inside. Even mold may appear underneath.
When choosing a bed, customs also influence.
Anyone who has spent a lot of time abroad often uses a very tall mattress with a soft coat and will have trouble feeling good on a lower, harder surface.
"Almost all the hockey players who came back from the NHL complained that they didn't sleep here as well."
"For their crushed shoulders, heels and hips they needed mattresses with a soft layer of viscoelastic."
"These types of mattresses are also recommended for people with diabetes than time nervous system problems, so they get bad information from the joints and skin," explains Sylva Hadamcziková, who specializes in quilted furniture.
Many hockey players, like other customers, have long preferred viscoelastic mattresses.
"Today there is no problem, because they have these suitable Tempur and the Italians Magniflex, but also the Czech brand Tropico."
You no longer have to be an NHL player to appreciate the viscoelastic.
This "miracle" works in a very simple way.
It optimizes its rigidity and shape depending on the heat absorbed or adapts to its body heat.
Nothing exerts pressure; during the night, it will not go around like after a hard game.
He just sleeps better.
The viscoelastic also functions as a protection against sores.
When choosing the size of the mattress, add to its height the length of its feet, that is, between 21 and 34 cm.
A man or woman with a height of about 180 cm will need a bed between 210 and 220 cm.
The minimum width for one person should be, in a double room, 90 cm, in total 180 cm.
In the case of single rooms, for example single rooms, at least 120 to 140 cm is recommended.
For a possible visit to be comfortable too.
"If not, a simple rule can be applied to calculate the width: when lying on your back, you should have your hands comfortably shrunk towards your elbows," advises engineer Helena Prokopová, an expert from Cechu čalouníků to dekoratérů, who has been dealing with the problem of healthy sleep and furniture ergonomics for many years, a subject he teaches in specialized schools.
In the double rooms, each one needs its own box box and mattress, so during the purchase you have to pay attention to combine the height of the mattresses.
Otherwise, it will be necessary to mount the bed soles at different heights, which is not always possible in all beds.
The foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, the models with the interior of springs a minimum of 15 cm, of which at least three centimeters are for the layer that adapts to the shapes and softens.
"When touching it by hand or when sitting on the mattress, the springs should certainly not be noticed," warns Helena Prokopová.
Each mattress requires a certain type of box spring.
The fully padded bedrooms, in which the mattress and base are like Siamese, make no sense in the bedroom.
Mattresses breathe badly and you can’t wash their cover, which is often done today.
And, since every night we sweat between 0.2 and 0.75 l of sweat, it is clear that after about five or seven years the mattress will begin to remind us of a large (and congested) sieve.
For this reason, specialists reject slogans that talk about a mattress life of up to 25 years or even a lifetime guarantee.
However, everything has a dog.
Therefore, the vendors give a tip: in the mattresses with a width of 120 or 140 cm, take care of the cleaning and washing of the cover, but better add a mattress protector that can be easily removed and washed.
Although mattress covers with zipper are currently manufactured throughout their perimeter, so when opened they stay in two parts (something very important for washing and the size of the washing machine!), their manipulation in the larger models (and by a single person) when lifting the mattress may seem like a fight between a fly weight and a heavy weight.
In bed, instead of a box spring, do you have a firm board?
Never!
At most for the beds designed for you to spend one night the visits.
However, you should make (if you do not already have them) ventilation holes in the table and should be used with a mattress with springs inside and a minimum height of 15 cm with the springs in bags (such as the German Taschenfederkern) and a soft layer.
Polyurethane mattresses should not be used on such bases.
For springs of non-articulable sheets and containing between 14 and 18 sheets, latex mattresses or sandwich mattresses (e.g., a combination of latex and coconut fiber) may be used, although a box spring with a greater number of sheets, 28 or more, in which the sheets of the lower back are reinforced and their stiffness can always be adjusted.
Articulable sheet beds should not be used with a spring mattress, since it does not react to recline.
In addition to the adjustment of the stiffness of the sheets, shoulder protection can also be used.
It is a special fixation of the sheets that allows to press or even tilt the sheets in such a way that they "surround" perfectly to the shoulders during sleep.
For men who have very wide shoulders, this is something very important.
They are even remembered by mattress manufacturers who, in the "male", began to use a softer area precisely around the shoulders.
They also remember women, for whom they put a softer area around their hips.
For the most demanding customers, there are box springs with cross or slat structure with the so-called multi-torque cushioning.
The pressure is distributed between different points and the voltage is lowered.
You should also keep in mind that even if you use the appropriate mattress and somier, if you use a bad pillow (large and "gritten"), most of the advantages will disappear.
The basic rule is simple: the pillow must hold the head and the corners can only reach the shoulders, so that the muscles of the same can be relaxed.
The recommended appropriate size is 50 x 60 cm, something normal for example in Scandinavia.
When lying on the side, the pillow should be at the same level (when combined with shoulder reinforcement or the softer area of the mattress) than shoulder height.
Modern mattresses have something to do with original straw-filled mattresses.
Manufacturers continue to use, more and more often, natural materials or at least mixtures.
In fact, biological mattresses are in fashion.
Petroleum-based raw materials, with which polyurethane foam is made, are filled with natural oils, for example castor or soybean.
In fact, virtually all known manufacturers use soy.
"Biological, in the case of mattresses, means that the center is made only of materials of natural origin," explains Petr Vašíček of the company Tropico Plus.
Also, natural substances are used during the manufacture of the mattress cover, one of the first aloe vera.
But you can also opt for microcapsules, which release a fresh aroma of forest or lavender.
There are also differences for men and women.
While men "cool down" with breeze plant extracts, so that the mattress cover absorbs heat and cools the body, women prefer to "heat" the sheath.
Red pepper extract improves blood circulation, so that women feel more warmth.
The favorites currently?
Mattresses made of cold foam, which are more porous, with an adapted cell structure, which makes them more permeable than normal polyurethane and offer more permeability.
The combination of various stiffnesses of cold foam and viscoelastic allows to manufacture mattresses of different areas that know perfectly where the head, shoulders and heels go.
A good quality mattress will cost you seven thousand crowns up.
Those who play a therapeutic role usually have a lower VAT, since they are considered as health means.
The first one to gain this advantage in the Czech Republic was Gumotex.
It is difficult to save on mattresses and bedstrips.
Sometimes you can approve the offers of the manufacturers or sellers, which sometimes offer two mattresses for the price of one.
For example, the Magniflex brand offers Duofreeze mattresses with a memory memory foam attached to the case by 11,990 crowns.
The second is available for free.
The era of viscoelastic with an open cellular structure and a high density began with the "cosmic" Tempur material.
It initially emerged as a material for NASA, because during the takeoffs the astronauts were subjected to a huge overload.
Tempur softens with heat and hardens with cold.
Therefore, the warm human body exerts a perfect effect and optimally adapts its pressure.
Therefore, it is ideal to prevent sores from occurring, but also to improve comfort during sleep.
The viscoelastic foam is not only used in mattresses, but also for medical devices, for example for pillows that are placed under the legs and relieve them, as well as their circulation.
Domestic manufacturers, for example, use Eucatherm C foam or Twinsaver and the like.
More and more parents are using people tracking devices to monitor their children
Fear for children leads more and more people to think about controlling them by GPS.
The system, initially designed for vehicle tracking, can also follow the movement of people and thus contribute, for example, in case of the disappearance of nine-year-old Anička Janatková.
At the moment the device is approximately the size of a matchbox, but it will soon be reduced to the size of a watch.
Many people were afraid of the case of the missing Anička and began to report on the means available to better protect her children.
Even at the cost of invading your privacy.
"We all try to tell ourselves that it's not about spying, but about another means to decrease the chances of a tragedy," says Petr Pilin of the company Macro Weil, one of the providers of tracking devices in the Czech market.
"I recognize that, in certain cases, such devices can be abused, for example if they get into someone's bag without their knowledge, but we have not yet encountered such cases."
“Most customers actually buy it for security reasons,” Pilin adds.
In his opinion, children should always know what the "box" is for and how it is used in case of emergency.
Child psychologist Dana Bočková warns of the fact that if the child does not want to take him, he will simply throw it away.
"Even younger children show great creativity when it comes to intentionally losing certain things if they want to prevent them from being controlled."
“Before, parents relied heavily on mobile phones, but these could be turned off as easily as the tracking device,” Bočková says.
In his opinion, it is debatable if in case of attack such a device is really useful.
"If it is a prepared kidnapping, the author will practically always check if the child carries any type of electronic device that can reveal his location."
"Now is the phone."
"As the use of tracking devices is extended, it will also look for them, since their sale will undoubtedly be done with a lot of advertising."
“In such cases, criminals always go one step ahead of the police,” the psychologist says.
However, he adds that such devices can help in the event of an improvised attack by a paedophile.
According to Robert Čech of the company RC Monitoring, which offers tracking services for both vehicles and people, even if, after an attack, the tracking device is immediately destroyed, its presence can help.
"The device can be configured to regularly send the position after a certain period."
"If you suffer damage, you will at least facilitate the last position of the person in question."
“The more expensive devices have a tilt meter integrated, so if the person simply slips and stays motionless, the device will immediately issue a warning with the position in question,” Čech says.
