According to Pilin of Macro Weil, for that reason tests are currently being carried out with devices that look like a digital clock.
"In addition, they will have the added advantage that a potential assailant may not identify the device."
"Or to identify it after a certain time, which can make the police win time."
Although tracking devices are worn on the wrist or hanging, they will continue to use the same technology used for vehicle tracking.
