The army has enough wicks to surround the entire Czech Republic. But they only last two years
The Czech army bought 445 kilometers of wick to light explosives.
Last year, the Ministry of Defense added 224 kilometers of fuse to its arsenal.
Therefore, they have stock for 225 years.
The problem is that the wick life is two years, four at most.
The army bought the wick for explosives from the STV Group, a. s. for forty million kroner.
General staff responded to MF DNES by justifying the purchase of such a huge amount of wick by saying that soldiers need for training maneuvers 60 kilometers of wick a year.
According to the calculations of the army pyrotechnics, with whom MF DNES contacted, it is decided, however, that, in such a case, they should perform such maneuvers with frequent use of explosives each year also all the generals, high command officers, and even secretaries and cleaners.
They didn’t want exempt or the Minister of Defense Alexandr Vondr and the army captain Vlastimil Picek.
Only in this way could it be justified for the army to spend sixty kilometers of wick.
Such length is equivalent to 25,000 explosions.
Even if so, the army would have enough stocks for more than ten years.
