Moelis and Co., which has already received 1.2 million dollars, will get a payment of 9.5 million dollars.
Cooper’s companies, which have been raising US$375,000 per month for their company management services, will receive a “successful hours” of US$4 million.
Barber and Birnbaum plan to resume production on MGM, which released only one film this year, and assembled an annual slate of seven or eight films coming out in 2012.
