It seems that President Zapatero has also understood this and his double manifesto (the reforms promised after the meeting last Saturday with the big companies and yesterday’s announcement of new measures) suggests that, despite the criticism of Merkel, the thesis has been opened that we must put order at home.
But the red line that Germany has drawn there is, and it doesn’t look like they’re going to move it.
And, among the possibilities that are contemplated, that of leaving a monetary zone too crowded from unserious countries, cannot be excluded.
